“People think that you’re gonna come out, be a one hit wonder, and finished. You gotta prove ‘em wrong.”- Takeoff 🕊️ 

2022

Thank you family, friends, and clients. 2022 was a tough year for so many. We made it✨

My introduction started with a reality show on OWN. “How was it?” Crazy but I’m glad I did it. And though, I don’t think the premise of us coming together will come to pass, we inspired homeownership and so many careers in real estate. *Love you ladies*

I sold my first house in March. By June I wanted to throw the whole year away, retire, and become a housewife. By July, God tapped me on the shoulder and said Nah, “Watch this...”. 
By December, I’d grossed over 35% higher than in 2021 as a Top Producer. More importantly, it was a blessing to help each and every client accomplish homeownership and sales goals. Thank you 🙏🏽. Going into 2023, we’re unstoppable with closings already on the books.

Personal Highlights: 
•We celebrated our 10 year wedding anniversary. 
•Our children are kind, healthy, and thriving honor students. 
•Most memorable vacation: Big Sky, Montana. 
•My brother came home. 
•Family and friends are still with me. 
•I gained almost 30 lbs of soft life high vibration weight… 
.•You helped me become a better woman, wife, mother, and professional. Thank you from my heart. 

Bye ✌🏽 2022, 2023 grant us your favor… 
Tiana Harrison

“Lord, guide me…” 

Ok guys, been gone -ish. Been in my Word. Been in the gym, in my husbands face, working, and enjoying my children. 

If you haven’t prayed for alignment, stop. Somebody needs to hear this. 

If you’re inside 2023 and you have not prayed for alignment, take a moment. Being aligned with priorities, in relationships, in business, is extremely important for your spiritual, mental, and physical health. [Balance]

Watch the things and people who manifest in your life. Watch the right doors close, watch better opportunities open up. Watch relationships mend, toxicity vanish. Watch your children accomplish great feats. Alignment leads to progress, prosperity, and success for all who are linked together.

**Two separate first-time homebuyers, one goal, one prayer.

Built by Award-winning luxury home builder Sharp Residential, a Toll Brothers Company.

✨Modern with a Refined Perspective. Located in Cumming’s highly sought after Westfall Swim-Tennis Community a coastal inspired estate with four sided brick and curated design finishes awaits. Built by Award-winning luxury home builder Sharp Residential, a Toll Brothers Company, the Rosehill III features luxurious finishes from top to bottom. More than six thousand square feet of interiors are introduced by a two-story foyer, formal study and elegant dining room. The attention to detail continues with warm, wide-planked, hardwoods and lofty ceilings throughout. The designer-tiled fireplace, bow windows, and coffered finish are as sophisticated as the homes sleek and modern gourmet kitchen. Grand pendant lighting, custom quartz countertops, upgraded cabinetry, top of the line Kitchen Aid appliances, and a beautiful oversized center island overlook a cafe and fireside keeping room. The main level also features a guest bedroom with ensuite, friends entrance, and mudroom. Upstairs, the Primary suite radiates serenity and romance with a grand sitting room, a stunning spa bath, and expansive custom dressing room. Access a light-filled media loft and three spacious secondary bedrooms with ensuites and vaulted ceilings. Enhanced with a custom finished daylight basement, enjoy the perfectly appointed home theater, exercise studio, full stone bath, den, and custom bar nook. Complete with Phoenix Technology upgrades, PestBan, Three Car Garage, tons of space and storage. Positioned on almost a half acre lot, landscaped grounds lead to a fenced backyard, children’s playset and playhouse. Top Rated Forsyth Schools. Just five miles from 400, Shopping, and Dining. Minutes to desirable Halcyon and Avalon. Live your luxury. Welcome Home.

So many late nights and early early mornings studying. So many talks about priorities, building mental toughness, and why it’s important to have a strong work ethic. 

Every morning they arrived early and on time. Every morning they prayed before they jumped excitedly out the car. Some days started and ended better than others. Each child with individual struggles and great triumphs… But they didn’t give up and they excelled. This is a different world (🎶 than where I come from). 

Thank you to everyone who helps us especially my mother-in-love, fondly known as, Mrs. Amy. We couldn’t do what we do without you. Thank you to my mom who gives me occasional much needed kidless holiday breaks. 

There are a few quotes that I live by that I really wanted my kids to grasp this year: 

✨How you do anything is how you do everything. (Accountability and Responsibility) 
✨Do what you need to do so you can do what you want to do. (Priorities and Work Ethic)
✨Lead with grace. (Respect and Reverence)
✨ I will throw that iPad out the window, keep playing with me. (Honesty and Crazy)

10 years ago… Thank you @pazid for helping me that Sunday morning and Jill Petersen for everything you taught me about contracts and negotiations and being on the other side of the deal that real estate school could never teach. 

3 Quick Short Lessons…
1) Know your office systems/where to access tools, resources, and forms. Systems can vary by brokerage and agent. (For example, dotloop, remine, authentisign, etc.) Any other day of the week at any time someone would have been able to help.. Everything happens the way it’s supposed to. 
2) One of my biggest pet peeves and tell-tell signs that I might be working with a new agent is when their special stips are unrealistic and don’t include who, where, when, and how. Know your special stipulations! Had Jill never came for me that Sun morning I might not know this to be as vital. It didn’t stop me from immediately paying Jill’s methods forward in future negotiations. Markets shift so asking for everything, every time might be unrealistic.. Be knowledgeable, understand the goals of your client, and leverage. 
3) Real Estate is business not personal. As a professional it is my responsibility to get us across the finish line. For my clients, Jill’s offer and long list of stips was offensive. Watch out for scenarios that cloud judgement. There are times when fires have to be extinguished that clients should never know about. It’s easy to get caught up in the drama of a deal and want to share that info so the client knows you’d go to hell and back for them but the reality is an agents focus should always be a smooth transaction for the client. State the facts not your opinion. Let’s review and analyze all terms and conditions of the offer, see what makes sense and what doesn’t. Never be afraid to say no, strike-through, negotiate, or renegotiate. I’ve worked with excellent professionals and horrible professionals. Jill was excellent.
